-- Bon-Ton May same-store sales up 1.2 percent
-- 
-- Tue Jun 5, 2007 4:39pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/05/us-bontonstores-sales-idUSN0530760320070605

 

 ATLANTA  (Reuters) - Bon-Ton Stores Inc. ( BONT.O ) said on Tuesday that sales at stores open at least a year rose 1.2 percent in May as apparel goods saw a rebound. 

 The apparel and furnishings retailer said same-store sales at its Carson Pirie Scott chain rose 4.9 percent for the month, while Bon-Ton comparable-store sales fell 5.3 percent. Weak categories included fashion accessories and furniture, the company said in a statement. In 2006, Bon-Ton doubled its size by buying the Northern Department Store Group, or Carson's, from Saks Inc. SKS.N It also bought five Parisian outlets from Belk. The York, Pennsylvania, company now operates nearly 280 stores under names such as Bon-Ton, Carson Pirie Scott, Boston Store and Elder-Beerman. Total sales for the four weeks ended June 2 rose 1 percent to $234.7 million. The company said total sales for the year to date were up 22 percent to $972.3 million.